#. <section class="sutta" id="sn13.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn13.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 13"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 13"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Abhisamayavagga"
msgstr "1. Comprehension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn13.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Dutiyasambhejjaudakasutta"
msgstr "4. Where the Waters Flow Together (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn13.4:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, "
"Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge."

# Alas, not so theoretical any more: http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2016/may/18/india-set-to-start-massive-project-to-divert-ganges-and-brahmaputra-rivers
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, taṃ udakaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ "
"gaccheyya ṭhapetvā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that water dried up and evaporated except for two or three drops."

msgctxt "sn13.4:1.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn13.4:1.5"
msgid ""
"katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ "
"yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Which is more: the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, "
"or the two or three drops left?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn13.4:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ sambhejjaudakaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated is "
"certainly more."

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.2"
msgid "appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhāni."
msgstr "The two or three drops left are tiny."

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.3"
msgid ""
"Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ "
"upenti sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā "
"udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Compared to the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, it’"
"s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”"

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.4"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done "
"with is more …”"

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.5"
msgid "dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn13.4:2.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
